\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs20\b0\i0 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93Dad?\u8221\'94 he repeated, }{\f0\fs24\b0 Nagano\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s grin faltered, replaced by a look of confusion.  his tone incredulous. \u8220\'93What are you talking about? I\u8217\'92m not your dad.\u8221\'94}
\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki shook her head, trying to clear the fog in her mind. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93No, I mean\u8230\'85 you\u8217\'92re\u8230\'85\u8221\'94 She trailed off, unsure how to explain. How could she tell him that she was his daughter from the future? He would never believe her.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Nagano tilted his head, studying her with a mixture of curiosity and concern. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Are you feeling okay?\u8221\'94 he asked. \u8220\'93You look like you\u8217\'92ve seen a ghost.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki forced a weak smile, though her heart was still racing. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I\u8217\'92m\u8230\'85 I\u8217\'92m fine,\u8221\'94 she said, though her voice betrayed her. \u8220\'93I just\u8230\'85 I think I need to sit down.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Nagano nodded, his easygoing demeanor returning. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Alright, let\u8217\'92s find a place to sit. You look like you\u8217\'92ve had a rough morning.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 As they walked, Haruki\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s mind was a whirlwind of emotions. She had found her father\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 or rather, the boy who would one day become her father. But he was so different from the man she knew. So\u8230\'85 alive. So full of life.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 And yet, the thought of what lay ahead for him\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 for both of them\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 filled her with a deep, aching sadness. She didn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t know how, but she had to find a way to change things. To make sure that the boy in front of her didn\u8217\'92t lose the light in his eyes.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 But for now, all she could do was follow him, her heart heavy with the weight of the future.}
