\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 -o-}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki sat on a piece of concrete pipe, her legs dangling as she watched the boys play a makeshift game of baseball. There were four of them, their laughter loud and carefree as they swung bats and chased after the ball. Nearby, four motorcycles were parked, their sleek designs a stark contrast to the simplicity of the game.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 The girl sitting next to her\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 a cheerful, dark-haired girl with a bright smile\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 handed her a carton of apple juice. Haruki took it, glancing at the unfamiliar brand name before sticking the straw in and taking a sip. It was sweet and refreshing, a small comfort in the midst of her confusion.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 The girl opened her mouth to start a conversation, but Haruki interrupted her, her words slightly muffled by the straw in her mouth. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93If you turned out to be Honoka Fujiyama\u8230\'85 I\u8217\'92m going to lose my mind.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 The girl blinked, her brow furrowing in confusion. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Honoka Fujiyama?\u8221\'94 she repeated. \u8220\'93You mean Honoka Aoki from Class 1A?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki froze, the carton of juice halfway to her mouth.\~}{\f0\fs24\b0\i1 Aoki.}{\f0\fs24\b0 \~That was her mother\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s maiden name. Of course. Her mother hadn\u8217\'92t taken her father\u8217\'92s surname yet. She was still Honoka Aoki in this time.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 The girl tilted her head, studying Haruki with a curious expression. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93What\u8217\'92s your name, by the way? I\u8217\'92m Sakura Emasu.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki hesitated, her mind racing. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Haruki\u8230\'85 Haruki Fujiyama,\u8221\'94 she said finally, her voice quiet.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Sakura\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s eyes widened in surprise. \u8220\'93Oh, are you and Naga-kun related?\u8221\'94 she asked, gesturing toward Nagano, who was currently arguing with one of the other boys over a questionable call.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki stared at her, her frustration bubbling to the surface. She didn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t know how to answer that question. Was she related to him? Technically, yes. But how could she explain that to someone who had no idea about the future\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 about who Nagano would become, about who\~}{\f0\fs24\b0\i1 she}{\f0\fs24\b0 \~was?}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Without a word, Haruki stood up, crumpled the empty juice carton in her hand, and threw it toward a nearby trash can. It missed, bouncing off the rim and landing on the ground. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I don\u8217\'92t know!\u8221\'94 she said, her voice tinged with frustration.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Sakura blinked, taken aback by Haruki\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s outburst. \u8220\'93Uh\u8230\'85 okay,\u8221\'94 she said slowly, her tone cautious. \u8220\'93You don\u8217\'92t have to get mad about it.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki sighed, running a hand through her hair. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I\u8217\'92m not mad,\u8221\'94 she said, though her voice still carried an edge. \u8220\'93I\u8217\'92m just\u8230\'85 confused.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Sakura studied her for a moment, then shrugged. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Well, if you say so. But you know, Naga-kun\u8217\'92s a good guy. If you\u8217\'92re related, you\u8217\'92re lucky.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki didn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t respond. She just sat back down, her eyes fixed on Nagano as he laughed and joked with his friends. He was so different from the man she knew\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 so carefree, so full of life. It was hard to believe that this was the same person who would one day become her stern, distant father.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 As she watched him, a strange mix of emotions swirled inside her\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 frustration, sadness, and a flicker of something she couldn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t quite name. Hope, maybe. Or determination.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 She didn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t know how she had ended up here, or why, but she knew one thing for sure: she wasn\u8217\'92t going to waste this chance. She was going to find out what had happened to her parents\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 to\~}{\f0\fs24\b0\i1 these}{\f0\fs24\b0 \~versions of them\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 and maybe, just maybe, she could change things.}
